# Package Manager Rules

## Use pnpm for All Package Management
This project uses `pnpm` as the package manager. All package management and script execution should be done using `pnpm` commands.

## Package Installation
- Use `pnpm install` to install dependencies
- Use `pnpm add <package>` to add dependencies
- Use `pnpm add -D <package>` to add dev dependencies
- Use `pnpm remove <package>` to remove dependencies

## Running Scripts
- Use `pnpm run <script>` or `pnpm <script>` to run npm scripts
- Available scripts:
  - `pnpm build` - Build the project
  - `pnpm dev` - Run development build with watch mode
  - `pnpm test` - Run tests
  - `pnpm test:watch` - Run tests in watch mode
  - `pnpm lint` - Lint the code

## Running Commands
- Use `pnpm dlx <command>` instead of `npx <command>`
- Example: `pnpm dlx typescript --version` instead of `npx typescript --version`

## Version Management
- Use `pnpm version patch|minor|major` for version bumps
- Do NOT use `npm version` or `yarn version`

